<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3053] Potential deadlock if event handler throws Throwable and is bypassing timeout handling</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3053</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If an event handler is bypassing the timeout handling (by configuration) and throws a throwable (like IllegalStateException), this can cause deadlocks as this is never catched and the internal state of the handlers goes out of sync.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12515247">FELIX-3053</key>
            <summary>Potential deadlock if event handler throws Throwable and is bypassing timeout handling</summary>
