                            <comment id="13070447" author="cziegeler" created="Mon, 25 Jul 2011 11:56:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With ususal timeout handling, this can&apos;t happen as the thread executor catches Throwables.&lt;br/&gt;
Added catching of throwables to the handler task in revision 1150645&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13070492" author="cziegeler" created="Mon, 25 Jul 2011 13:25:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Obviously, the description above was wrong: this happens only if an Error is thrown - and IllegalStateException is not an error but an exception which is handled correctly&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
